<item>
            <title>[BEAM-13081] Portable representation of &quot;packed bitset indicating null fields&quot; in beam Row format is not compatible with jvm representations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-13081</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JVM RowCoder strips trailing 0s from the null-value bitmap, while both python and go expect all bits to be present in the encoded bitmap.&#160; This causes index-out-of-range errors when trying to decode a row encoded on the JVM in other languages in some circumstances.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, given a Row with 10 nullable fields, if the first 8 are null and the last two are set, the row will fail to decode in python, because the nullable bitmap will only have 1 byte, but the python coder expects 2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As discussed in the thread, the best solution here is probably to change the python (and go) coders to accept truncated nullable bitmaps.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More discussion here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r2f148e29902bda8bb0ff7106fffb8a5494295450827ad7fd17289383%40%3Cdev.beam.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r2f148e29902bda8bb0ff7106fffb8a5494295450827ad7fd17289383%40%3Cdev.beam.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
